         <text>E2open</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-578E53C2-12B0-464B-945F-D352E7C62CCC" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>If the vendor is blocked, they will not be allowed to participate in sourcing events.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-65FADA13-46B4-4CD1-9BFF-0668ECB0FD2F" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>1.Vendor block information flows from Graphite to Realtio to ECC currently

2.In the to-be process, Realtio and ECC will be replaced by MDG and S4

3.In the to-be process, vendor block will be applied on the vendor ID (BP ID) and the same information will be sent to S4 from MDG and the same block 
information will be sent to Ariba from S4

4.Vendor ID will be blocked in Ariba from the data sent from MDG to S4 to Ariba</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-7E8A8490-42F3-43B0-8ABD-2BE003162575" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-left"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-right"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Flow has been migrated to BIC. Please inform the process steward Dhanwantry, Kalyan R &lt;kalyan.r.dhanwantry@intel.com&gt; and BPM Champions D'Elia, Traci &lt;traci.delia@intel.com&gt;,Newman, Jennifer &lt;jennifer.newman@intel.com&gt;of any design changes that occur within the flow moving forward. This will enable us to reflect those changes in the BIC and WIKI business process documentation.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
   </process>
